<HEAD>Six Killed in Plane Crash</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 5th graf to CORRECT hometown of pilot to Georgia sted Florida
and spelling of Sanders' first name to Terry sted Harry</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MAYFIELD, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A twin-engine plane crashed in an open field
in rain and fog Friday night, killing all six people aboard, police
said.
   The Beechcraft BE-10 apparently was headed for a landing at the
Mayfield-Graves County airport when it crashed northeast of the
site, a state police dispatcher said. She blamed poor weather on the
crash.
   ``This is a real nasty night,'' said the dispatcher, who declined
to be identified.
   She said the plane was arriving from Florida, but had no details.
   The victims were identified as pilot John Haag, of Georgia; and
Mayfield residents Charles Yancey and his wife, Belinda; Terry
Sanders and his wife, Melissa, and the Rev. Charles Nelson. The
dispatcher did not have ages.
   Federal investigators were expected to arrive at the site in the
southwest corner of Kentucky on Saturday, the dispatcher said.
