<FIRST>r i PM-Philippines-Landslide     09-16 0206</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Philippines-Landslide,0212</SECOND>
<HEAD>At Least 14 Killed In Slide</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto MLA1,2</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Monsoon rains loosened earth in a
quarry in a Manila suburb, triggering a landslide today that buried
more than a dozen houses in a nearby squatter colony. At least 14
people were killed, officials said.
   Zenaida Santa Ana, head social worker of the Department of Social
Welfare and Development for the Manila area, said the landslide
occurred at 6:00 a.m. in the village of Tunasan in Muntinglupa, just
south of the capital.
   Ms. Santa Ana said soldiers, police officers and civilian
volunteers dug up 14 bodies under the tons of mud, rock and debris.
Seven of the eight people found alive were in serious condition, she
said.
   The landslide destroyed at least 14 shanties.
   Ms. Santa Ana said 68 families living near the quarry were
evacuated to a nearby chapel because of fears that additional rain
may trigger another landslide.
   Ten hours after the incident, rescuers still were searching for
one male resident of the area, she said.
   She said the rescue had been slow because the area is an interior
village and is not accessible to large digging equipment. Most
rescuers were using using their hands, picks, shovels and pails.
</TEXT>
