<SECOND>PM-Contract Bridge, 1st Ld-Writethru,a0455,0212</SECOND>
<HEAD>United States in Semi-Finals</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES thruout with today's games; no pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PERTH, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Australia defeated France, 23-7 today to
move into a strong position in its battle to qualify for a semifinal
berth in the Bermuda Bowl contract bridge team world championship.
   The top teams in the 14-match round-robin will advance to
Monday's semifinals in which the Unites States and Poland, winners
of their continental championships, were automatic qualifiers.
   Brazil increased its lead over the field by blitzing Taiwan and
seems assured of one of the semifinal berths, with two matches to
go. The battle for the other is between Australia and France, and
Australia now leads by 11 points; the maximum score for a match is
25.
   In the Venice Cup women's world team championship, the
Netherlands suffered its first loss, but Australia still fell from
second to third place despite its 21-9 victory. Canada, which was
tied with Australia at the start of the day's play, blitzed Brazil
and pulled four points ahead of Australia.
   The Netherlands already has qualified for the semifinals; the
battle for the other position is between Canada and Australia.
   In that championship, the United States and West Germany,
continental champions, were automatic qualifiers.
