<FIRST>r i AM-BRF-Oktoberfest     09-16 0133</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF-Oktoberfest,0137</SECOND>
<HEAD>World's Biggest Beer Bash Opens; Milk Bar Allowed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MUNICH, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The 156th Oktoberfest, the world's
biggest annual beer bash, opened Saturday in Munich with a milk bar
joining rows of beer tents for the first time.
   The traditional 12-gun salute reverberated across Munich as Mayor
Georg Kronawitter tapped the first keg of beer.
   City officials expect more than 6 million tourists from all over
the world for the 16-day festival and authorities said most of the
32,000 hotel rooms in the Bavarian capital had been booked months in
advance.
   The traditional quart stein of beer costs about $3.50 this year,
slightly more than last year.
   After allowing alcohol-free beer in 1986, festival organizers
finally gave in to dairy farmers' five-year campaign to set up a
milk bar.
</TEXT>
