<HEAD>Ten Killed In Balcony Collapse</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALEXANDRIA, Egypt (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A crowded second-floor balcony of an old
house collapsed on to a street wedding procession, killing 10 people
and injuring 17, a police official said Saturday.
   He said three children, six women and a man were killed but he
did not know how many of the victims were on the balcony and how
many were in the street below.
   The accident occurred Thursday in the working-class district of
Karmouz as a wedding group was passing through the streets of this
Mediterranean port city.
   Balconies overlooking the street were crammed with onlookers,
many of whom danced and clapped as the newlyweds led the procession,
according to police.
   The stone balcony of a four-story house suddenly crashed to the
street below, apparently because it was overloaded, the official
said.
   He reported the bride and bridegroom were not injured.
