<FIRST>r i AM-China-Typhoon     09-16 0131</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-China-Typhoon,0136</SECOND>
<HEAD>Typhoon Kills at Least 48 in Coastal China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One of the most powerful typhoons in decades has
killed 48 people, left 26 missing, and flooded large areas in the
coastal Chinese province of Zhejiang, the official news agency
reported Saturday.
   Typhoon Vera also injured 190 people in the area south of
Shanghai, the Xinhua News Agency said.
   Rains flooded the port city of Shujiang, the report said. Also
inundated were 163,000 acres of rice paddies and 32,000 acres of
orange orchards, Xinhua said.
   The report did not say how many people were evacuated.
   Zhejiang suffered 122 deaths and economic losses of $286 million
from torrential rains in July.
   In 1988, about 400 people in the province lost their lives in
typhoons, heavy rains and flooding.
</TEXT>
