<DATELINE>BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Colombia's army and national police
braced for attacks by cocaine traffickers today, a national holiday
called Day of Love and Friendship.
   Seven bombs exploded in three cities Friday, injuring eight
people.
   No one claimed responsibility, but a series of such attacks over
the past month have been linked to drug lords at war with the
government.
   The Defense Ministry put the country's 200,000-man army and
80,000 national police on alert, canceling all leaves and keeping
the forces on standby.
